Tariff Submitter: Arroyo Solar LLC
FERC Tariff Program: FERC FPA Electric Tariff Tariff Title: Rate Schedules and Tariffs Tariff Record Proposed Effective Date: December 31, 2022 Tariff Record Title: FERC Electric Rate Schedule No. 1 Option Code: A
SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this ???Agreement???), is entered into as of July 26, 2021 (the ???Effective Date???), by and between Arroyo Solar LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and permitted assigns, ???Arroyo Solar???) and Arroyo Energy Storage LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and permitted assigns, ???Arroyo Energy Storage,??? and together with Arroyo Solar, the ???Parties??? and each a ???Party???).
RECITALS
WHEREAS, Arroyo Energy Center LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, is the owner of all of the membership interests of Arroyo Solar and Arroyo Energy Storage;
WHEREAS, Arroyo Solar is developing and will own and operate a 300 MWac ground-mounted photovoltaic solar power generation facility located in McKinley County, New Mexico (the ???Arroyo Solar Project???);
WHEREAS, Arroyo Energy Storage is developing and will own and operate a battery energy storage facility with a nameplate capacity of approximately 150 MWac/ 600 MWh (the ???Arroyo Energy Storage Project???), integrated into the Arroyo Solar Project and utilizing the Shared Facilities (as defined below) to interconnect under Arroyo Solar???s interconnection agreement (together with the Arroyo Solar Project, the ???Projects??? and each a ???Project???);
WHEREAS Arroyo Solar and Public Service Company of New Mexico (???PNM???) are parties to that Power Purchase Agreement ??? Arroyo Solar Facility, dated as of June 27, 2019, as amended by that certain First Amendment, dated as of June 2, 2020, as further amended by that Second Amendment, dated as of September 22, 2020, as further amended by that Third Amendment, dated as of April 27, 2021, as further amended by that certain letter agreement amending Section 10.11 of the PPA, effective as of June 11, 2021 (the ???PPA???), and as and as further amended, supplemented or otherwise modified from time to time;
WHEREAS Arroyo Energy Storage and PNM are parties to that Energy Storage Agreement ??? Arroyo Energy Storage, dated as of June 27, 2019, as amended by that certain First Amendment, dated as of June 2, 2020, as further amended by that Second Amendment, dated as of September 22, 2020, as further amended by that Third Amendment, dated as of April 27, 2021 (the ???ESA???), and as further amended, supplemented or otherwise modified from time to time;
WHEREAS, Arroyo Solar entered into and is the defined ???Interconnection Customer??? under that certain Standard Large Generator Interconnection Agreement, by and between itself and PNM, originally dated as of June 4, 2021 (the ???Arroyo Solar GIA???) which provides for interconnection to the Transmission System (as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA) of the ???300 MW (solar and battery energy storage system) Large Generating Facility??? (as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA, Appendix A);
WHEREAS, interconnection rights under the Arroyo Solar GIA are necessary both for Arroyo Solar to satisfy its obligations under the PPA and for Arroyo Energy Storage to satisfy its obligations under the ESA;
WHEREAS, Arroyo Solar owns certain personal property, fixtures, equipment, facilities (including the Interconnection Customer???s Interconnection Facilities, as identified in the Arroyo Solar GIA, Appendix A,), and other rights described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the ???Shared Facilities???) that are necessary to interconnect the Projects to the electric transmission system of PNM;
WHEREAS, Arroyo Solar and Arroyo Energy Storage are entering into this Shared Facilities Agreement as contemplated under the PPA, the ESA and Arroyo Solar GIA to (i) allow the Arroyo Energy Storage Project to use Shared Facilities and Transmission Provider???s Interconnection Facilities (???TPIF???), as described in the Arroyo Solar GIA, to interconnect to the electric transmission system of PNM under the terms and conditions of the Arroyo Solar GIA and (ii) allow Arroyo Energy Storage to use the Shared Facilities and TPIF as necessary for it to be able to operate its Project and to perform its obligations under the ESA and to deliver to and receive energy from (x) the Arroyo Solar Project and (y) PNM; and
WHEREAS, the Arroyo Solar GIA requires that this Shared Facilities Agreement be incorporated, by amendment, into the Arroyo Solar GIA;
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
AGREEMENT
1. TERM; EARLY TERMINATION
1.1 Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, or (b) pursuant to Section 1.2 of this Agreement.
1.2 Early Termination. This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by any Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party (except for obligations accruing prior to the termination), upon the termination of the Arroyo Solar GIA.
2. GRANT OF INTERCONNECTION AND SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS
2.1 Grant. Arroyo Solar hereby grants to Arroyo Energy Storage, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the following: (a) all rights necessary and convenient under the Arroyo Solar GIA to interconnect the Arroyo Energy Storage Project to the Transmission System as part of the Large Generating Facility defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA; and (b) the non-
exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with the Interconnection Service (as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA) received by Arroyo Energy Storage from PNM, and ownership, operation and maintenance of the Arroyo Energy Storage Project. The grant of rights under this Agreement by Arroyo Solar to Arroyo Energy Storage is made only to the extent that such rights do not limit in any material respect the ability of Arroyo Solar, as the Interconnection Customer, to comply with the terms and conditions of the Arroyo Solar GIA. Further, nothing in this Agreement alters any rights and obligations under Section 5.1(A) of the ESA.
2.2 Essential Nature. Arroyo Solar hereby acknowledges that the right of Arroyo Energy Storage to access and utilize Arroyo Solar???s rights under the Arroyo Solar GIA and the Shared Facilities are essential to the injection of electric energy from the Arroyo Energy Storage Project to the transmission system of PNM and withdrawal of energy, if any, by the Arroyo Energy Storage Project from the transmission system.
2.3 Vesting. The right to access and utilize Arroyo Solar???s rights under the Arroyo Solar GIA and the Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Arroyo Solar to Arroyo Energy Storage shall vest in Arroyo Energy Storage as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold or other interest or rights in the Shared Facilities.
3. NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS
3.1 Nature of Services. The Parties acknowledge that the grant of rights under this Agreement by Arroyo Solar to Arroyo Energy Storage is required by the Arroyo Solar GIA and the ESA and is made for the purpose of enabling the energy from Arroyo Energy Storage to reach the transmission system of PNM, and for energy from the transmission system of PNM, if any, to reach Arroyo Energy Storage. Subject to Section 2.1 herein, the grant of rights under this Agreement by Arroyo Solar to Arroyo Energy Storage is not intended, for the avoidance of doubt, (i) to adversely affect the operations of the Arroyo Solar Project in any respect or (ii) to limit the ability of any Party to perform its obligations under any agreement, as the same may hereafter be modified or amended, that such Party has entered into or enters into after the date hereof.
3.2 Obligations of Arroyo Solar. Arroyo Solar shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner consistent with its obligations under the Arroyo Solar GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Arroyo Solar agrees to serve as the Shared Facilities Manager to:
(i) perform its obligations under this Agreement and its obligations as the Interconnection Customer under the Arroyo Solar GIA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable
Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the Arroyo Solar GIA;
(ii) comply with all provisions of the Arroyo Solar GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, payments due, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof);
(iii) serve as a single point of contact for PNM under the Arroyo Solar GIA, and to promptly provide to Arroyo Energy Storage any material notices it receives under the Arroyo Solar GIA from PNM; and
(iv) perform necessary maintenance on the Shared Facilities.
3.3 Obligations of Arroyo Energy Storage. Arroyo Energy Storage shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates Arroyo Solar???s performance under, and compliance with, the Arroyo Solar GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Arroyo Energy Storage agrees to:
(i) operate the Arroyo Energy Storage Project and perform its obligations under this Agreement and the Arroyo Energy Storage ESA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the Arroyo Solar GIA and the ESA;
(ii) facilitate Arroyo Solar???s compliance with all provisions of the Arroyo Solar GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as related to the Arroyo Energy Storage Project;
(iii) not take any action (or refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the Arroyo Solar GIA by Arroyo Solar;
(iv) use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of the Arroyo Energy Storage Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default by Arroyo Solar under the Arroyo Solar GIA, and if such default occurs or is determined by Arroyo Solar in good faith to be reasonably likely to result in such default, promptly assist Arroyo Solar in curing such default in accordance with the terms of the Arroyo Solar GIA;
(v) comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by Arroyo Solar, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the Arroyo Solar GIA;
(vi) provide Arroyo Solar with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of the Arroyo Energy Storage Project required for Arroyo Solar to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the Arroyo Solar GIA;
(vii) promptly provide to Arroyo Solar copies of all notices and instructions received by Arroyo Energy Storage that affect Arroyo Solar???s performance under the Arroyo Solar GIA; and
(viii) provide payment to Arroyo Solar within ten (10) business days following receipt of demand therefor for (a) its lost revenues any time the Arroyo Solar Project is curtailed, disconnected, or experiences an outage due to actions or inactions by Arroyo Energy Storage due to interconnection activities, operations and maintenance, or other reasons, with such lost revenues including all revenues that Arroyo Solar would have earned for energy, green attributes, capacity, or other products it would have sold under the applicable agreements to which it is a party, (b) availability incentive or bonus payments lost, or (c) other penalties, costs or charges incurred by Arroyo Solar, as a direct result of any interruptions or curtailments of output from the Arroyo Solar Project; in each case, such payments made or to be made by Arroyo Energy Storage shall be reduced by any insurance proceeds actually received by Arroyo Solar in connection with the events described in subclauses (a), (b) or (c) of this Section 3.3(viii).
3.4 No Joint and Several Liability between Arroyo Solar and Arroyo Energy Storage. The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject either Party to joint and several liability for any actions taken by the other Party.
3.5 Assignment or Transfer of Rights. Except as set forth in Section 9.5 hereof, Arroyo Solar and Arroyo Energy Storage, respectively, shall not assign or transfer any rights granted to such Party hereunder with regard to the Shared Facilities, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right with regard to the Shared Facilities, without the prior written consent of the other Party.
3.6 Interference. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities if the exercise of such rights would materially interfere with or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party.
3.7 Prior Written Consent. Except as set forth in this Agreement, without the prior written consent of such other Party, neither Party shall take any action that results in (i) the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights of the other Party or (ii) increases the obligations or responsibilities of the other Party, in each case, with respect to such Party???s access to, utilization of or reliance upon the Shared Facilities.
4. MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES; SUCCESSOR AGREEMENT; METERING
4.1 Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses.
(i) Arroyo Solar shall be solely responsible for the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities, including (a) the costs and expenses of the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities and of insuring the Shared Facilities, and (b) the costs that Arroyo Solar is responsible for under the Arroyo Solar GIA, including potential costs under Section 10.5 for operations and maintenance expenses.
(ii) Arroyo Solar and Arroyo Energy Storage shall each be liable to pay for the station power service of their respective Projects.
4.2 Successor Agreement. In the event that the Shared Facilities are no longer operated and maintained only by Arroyo Solar for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities.
4.3 Further Assurances. Each Party hereto covenants and agrees to promptly work in good faith to do and perform such other and further acts and things as the other Party hereto may reasonably request or as may be otherwise be necessary or proper to resolve the appropriate allocation of the following items among the Projects: (A) the energy output and usage of the applicable Projects, (B) associated losses, and (C) payments associated with the Projects??? energy output, usage, and losses.
5. CHANGE IN LAW
5.1 Change in Law. In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Shared Facilities, any of the Projects, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement.
6. CERTAIN COVENANTS
6.1 Authority and Operational Abilities. Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement.
6.2 Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Parties so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each such Project.
6.3 Adverse Events.
(i) If an operational issue arises at the Arroyo Solar Project or Arroyo Energy Storage Project that is reasonably expected to result in a material breach by Arroyo Solar of the Arroyo Solar GIA or this Agreement or if required to comply with any applicable Tariff requirements of PNM (as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA and the Arroyo Energy Storage ESA) (an ???Adverse Event???), Arroyo Solar shall curtail the Project that is causing the Adverse Event. In the event of such curtailment, energy deliveries to or withdrawals from the Point of Interconnection from the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall be limited as necessary until the Adverse Event has been cured in the reasonable judgment of Arroyo Solar.
(ii) If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event caused by either Project, Arroyo Solar incurs costs, expenses, or penalties of any kind (???AE Costs???), the Party owning the Project that caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for such AE Costs. In the event that both Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that Arroyo Solar, in its sole and absolute discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, Arroyo Solar shall be responsible for only its allocable portion of such applicable AE Costs and Arroyo Solar shall allocate the remaining AE Costs to Arroyo Energy Storage. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Arroyo Solar, as determined in its sole and absolute discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, Arroyo Solar shall be liable for 67% of such AE Costs and Arroyo Energy Storage shall be liable for 33% of such AE Costs.
7. MATERIAL BREACH; LIMITATIONS
7.1 Material Breach by any Party. In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party fails to promptly cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from the other, non-defaulting Party describing such breach, the non-defaulting Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the defaulting Party, or (ii) if Arroyo Solar is the non-breaching Party, suspend Arroyo Energy Storage???s access to all or any portion of the Shared Facilities for so long as such default shall be continuing and remain uncured. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in the event that a breach of this Agreement could give rise to a breach by Arroyo Solar pursuant to the terms of the Arroyo Solar GIA, the non-defaulting Party shall not be required to provide the defaulting Party with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to
exercise the remedies specified in clause (i) or (ii) above; provided, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender or investor of such Party. If a Party (or any lender or investor thereof) chooses to cure a Party???s default, the defaulting Party shall reimburse the non-defaulting Party (or such Party???s lender or investor) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by the non-defaulting Party (or such Party???s lender or investor) in curing such default.
7.2 Except for indemnification obligations related to third-party claims as provided for in Section 9.6 or as otherwise expressly provided for in this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages including, but not limited to, loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability.
8. FORCE MAJEURE
8.1 Force Majeure. Upon any occurrence beyond a Party???s reasonable control that prevents such Party from fulfilling an obligation under this Agreement and that would constitute an event of Force Majeure (as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA), such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The Party affected shall promptly give notice and the full particulars of such Force Majeure (as defined in the Arroyo Solar GIA) to the other Party in writing or by telephone as soon as reasonably possible after the occurrence of the cause relied upon. Telephone notices given pursuant to this article shall be confirmed in writing as soon as reasonably possible and shall specifically state full particulars of such Force Majeure, the time and date when such Force Majeure occurred and when such Force Majeure is reasonably expected to cease. The Party affected shall exercise due diligence to remove such disability with reasonable dispatch, but shall not be required to accede or agree to any provision not satisfactory to it in order to settle and terminate a strike or other labor disturbance.
9. MISCELLANEOUS
9.1 Authorization. Except as provided in Section 7.1, nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party.
9.2 Modification and Amendment. The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all Parties.
9.3 Waiver. The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of
such Party???s right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect.
9.4 Enforceability. Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof.
9.5 Assignment. No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party, including through a change of control of such Party, without the prior written consent of the other Party, provided, however, that (i) either Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to the same lender in connection with a financing or a refinancing of the Projects and (ii) prior written consent for a change of control of a Party shall not be required if such transaction provides for the transfer of control of Arroyo Solar and Arroyo Energy Storage to the same third party.
9.6 Indemnification. Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party???s performance or non- performance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of fraud, gross negligence, willful misconduct or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified Party.
9.7 Choice of Law, Jurisdiction and Waiver of Jury Trial
(i) This Agreement and the rights and obligations of the Parties hereunder will be governed pursuant to, and enforced, construed and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the State of New York without regard to principles of conflicts of laws (other than Section 5-1401 of the General Obligations Law of the State of New York). Venue for resolution of any disputes under this Agreement shall be New York County, New York.
(ii) Each of the Parties irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York for the purposes of any suit, action or other proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement, the transactions contemplated hereby, any provision hereof or the breach, performance, enforcement or validity or invalidity of this Agreement or any provision hereof (and agrees not to commence any suit, action or proceeding relating thereto except in such courts).
(iii) THE PARTIES HERETO EACH HEREBY KNOWINGLY, VOLUNTARILY AND INTENTIONALLY WAIVE THE RIGHT EACH MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY WITH RESPECT TO ANY PROCEEDINGS BASED HEREON, OR ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT, OR ANY COURSE OF CONDUCT, COURSE OF DEALING, STATEMENTS (WHETHER ORAL OR WRITTEN) OR ACTIONS OF EITHER PARTY TO THIS AGREEMENT. THIS PROVISION IS A MATERIAL INDUCEMENT FOR THE PARTIES TO ENTER INTO THIS AGREEMENT.
9.8 Inspection of Records. Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times.
9.9 Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof.
9.10 Section Headings. The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof.
9.11 Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument.
9.12 Specific Performance. The Parties hereto may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance. A facsimile or Portable Document Format (???.pdf???) signature page shall constitute an original for purposes hereof.
9.13 Obligation to Notify in Case of Termination. The Parties shall notify PNM within 10 business days if the Agreement is terminated
9.14 Insurance. At all times during the term of this Agreement, Arroyo Energy Storage shall maintain insurance as then required under the ESA and the Arroyo Solar GIA.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Shared Facilities Agreement to be executed as of the date first written above.

Arroyo Solar LLC
Market-Based Rate Wholesale Power Sale Tariff
1. Availability. Arroyo Solar LLC ("Seller") makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale. 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all sales of capacity, energy, or ancillary services by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sales shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Ancillary Services. Seller may make available to any purchaser the following ancillary services. a. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. b. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. c. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. d. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. e. MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (MISO) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. f. Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. g. Third Party Provider: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider???s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Seller has received (i) waiver of the accounting and reporting requirements contained in 18 C.F.R. Parts 41, 101 (with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects), and 141, except for section 141.15; (ii) waiver of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subparts B and C, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; and (iii) blanket authorization under 18 C.F.R. Seller???s tariff excludes market-based sales to customers located within the Puget Sound Energy Balancing Authority Area. See Puget Sound Energy, Inc., 181 FERC ?? 61,008 (2022). 8. Mitigated Sales: Sales of energy and capacity are permissible under this tariff in all balancing authority areas where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority. Sales of energy and capacity under this tariff are also permissible at the metered boundary between the Seller's mitigated balancing authority area and a balancing authority area where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority provided: (i) legal title of the power sold transfers at the metered boundary of the balancing authority area where the seller has market-based rate authority; and (ii) if the Seller sells at the metered boundary of a mitigated balancing authority area at market-based rates, then neither it nor its affiliates can sell into that mitigated balancing authority area from the outside. Seller must retain, for a period of five years from the date of the sale, all data and information related to the sale that demonstrates compliance with items (i) and (ii) above. 9. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 seller in the Central, Northeast, Northwest, Southeast, and Southwest Power Pool regions, as defined by 18 CFR ?? 35.36(a).
